{"alignment_id": "laozi-chapter-050__align-004", "work_id": "laozi", "section_id": "laozi-chapter-050", "alignment_type": "exact_or_near_exact", "confidence": 1.0, "order": 6, "section_unit": "chapter", "segment_type": "sentence", "alignment_granularity": "grouped", "is_coarse_alignment": false, "coarse_alignment_reason": null, "source_segment_count": 4, "target_segment_count": 1, "chinese_ref": "老子 50.6 - 老子 50.9", "chinese_text": "人之生，動之死地，亦十有三。夫何故？", "translation_ref": "老子 50.4", "translation_text": "There are also three in every ten whose aim is to live, but whose movements tend to the land (or place) of death. And for what reason?"}
{"alignment_id": "laozi-chapter-050__align-005", "work_id": "laozi", "section_id": "laozi-chapter-050", "alignment_type": "exact_or_near_exact", "confidence": 1.0, "order": 10, "section_unit": "chapter", "segment_type": "sentence", "alignment_granularity": "grouped", "is_coarse_alignment": false, "coarse_alignment_reason": null, "source_segment_count": 4, "target_segment_count": 2, "chinese_ref": "老子 50.10 - 老子 50.13", "chinese_text": "以其生生之厚。蓋聞善攝生者，陸行不遇兕虎，入軍不被甲兵；", "translation_ref": "老子 50.5 - 老子 50.6", "translation_text": "Because of their excessive endeavours to perpetuate life. But I have heard that he who is skilful in managing the life entrusted to him for a time travels on the land without having to shun rhinoceros or tiger, and enters a host without having to avoid buff coat or sharp weapon."}
{"alignment_id": "laozi-chapter-050__align-006", "work_id": "laozi", "section_id": "laozi-chapter-050", "alignment_type": "exact_or_near_exact", "confidence": 1.0, "order": 14, "section_unit": "chapter", "segment_type": "sentence", "alignment_granularity": "grouped", "is_coarse_alignment": false, "coarse_alignment_reason": null, "source_segment_count": 4, "target_segment_count": 1, "chinese_ref": "老子 50.14 - 老子 50.17", "chinese_text": "兕無所投其角，虎無所措其爪，兵無所容其刃。夫何故？", "translation_ref": "老子 50.7", "translation_text": "The rhinoceros finds no place in him into which to thrust its horn, nor the tiger a place in which to fix its claws, nor the weapon a place to admit its point. And for what reason?"}
{"alignment_id": "laozi-chapter-050__align-007", "work_id": "laozi", "section_id": "laozi-chapter-050", "alignment_type": "exact_or_near_exact", "confidence": 1.0, "order": 18, "section_unit": "chapter", "segment_type": "sentence", "alignment_granularity": "grouped", "is_coarse_alignment": false, "coarse_alignment_reason": null, "source_segment_count": 1, "target_segment_count": 1, "chinese_ref": "老子 50.18", "chinese_text": "以其無死地。", "translation_ref": "老子 50.8", "translation_text": "Because there is in him no place of death."}
